        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "improve(ios): guide first-run users into gateway onboarding",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFirst-time iOS users could open OpenClaw Mobile with no Gateway yet and land in an app that mostly assumed setup had already happened. That made the mobile app feel broken or half-live instead of clearly explaining that the phone connects to a Gateway running elsewhere.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis adds a first-run gateway onboarding path with three clear choices: explore a sample preview, set up OpenClaw Gateway, or enter an existing setup code. Preview mode now uses seeded sample data across the main iOS surfaces without marking real onboarding complete, and the setup path explains that the Gateway does the work while the phone stays lightweight.\n\nReview follow-up: configured or previously onboarded users who are temporarily offline now keep the Settings / Gateway diagnostics route from gateway CTAs and on launch, while true first-run and preview-mode setup CTAs still open onboarding. Explicit setup requests now start on the setup screen and cannot back into the first-run welcome choices. Preview approval examples are sample-only so they do not resolve through the real Gateway path.\n\nAI-assisted: yes. I understand the change and reviewed the final diff, simulator behavior, and validation output.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNew iOS users can understand the Gateway model from the first screen, preview what a mature OpenClaw workspace feels like, and then move into setup with platform-specific install guidance. Existing connected, configured, or previously onboarded users keep the normal Gateway settings and diagnostics path, while preview exploration stays clearly labeled and read-only.\n\n## Evidence\n\nVisual proof packet: https://github.com/Solvely-Colin/openclaw/releases/tag/ios-onboarding-proof-20260626-421e04c\n\n![iOS onboarding preview tour](https://github.com/Solvely-Colin/openclaw/releases/download/ios-onboarding-proof-20260626-421e04c/onboarding-preview-tour.gif)\n\nFocused validation:\n\n- iPhone 17 Pro simulator build/run succeeded through XcodeBuildMCP.\n- iOS simulator tests passed: 92 passed, 0 failed.\n  - `OpenClawTests/OnboardingStateStoreTests`\n  - `OpenClawTests/RootTabsPresentationTests`\n  - `OpenClawTests/RootTabsSourceGuardTests`\n- `git diff --check` produced no output.\n- Repo-local autoreview helper passed with Codex engine: no accepted/actionable findings after the review fixes.\n\nProof notes:\n\n- The proof release includes the route GIF, trimmed MP4, contact sheet, key screenshots for onboarding/preview/setup, `PR_PROOF.md`, and the latest simulator test log.\n- The setup screen includes Copy and Share entry points. Simulator automation did not present the iOS share sheet during capture, so that remains a manual visual check item if reviewers want share-sheet-specific proof.\n",
